{
  "doc_id": "27213",
  "text": "Our work is distinguished from other efforts to formalise the semantics of complex processor architectures [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , by its focus on a prototype architecture that is several years away from fabrication. We therefore deliberately focus on an idealised model. This enables rapid development, and leads to what we regard as the key value of our work: identifying fixes and improvements to the RSP design to be made at very little cost. In contrast, errors and bugs discovered late in the design cycle or errors that make it into silicon can be extremely expensive to fix or work around.",
